arch:property.oc:show_val: All the architectural elements of Chambers 2 and 3 and partial Chamber 1. Locus 6 West Buttress #1, Locus 5 East Buttress #1, Chamber 2 Locus 10 Floor, Chamber 2 West Wall Locus 13, Chamber 2 East Wall Locus 12, Chamber 3 Floor Locus 26, Locus 16 West Wall for the build-up of the Lower Temenos, Locus 17 West Retaining Wall under the West Wall, Vault Locus 15, Locus 22 East Chamber 3 Wall, East Buttress #2 Locus 19, West Buttress #2 Locus 18, and Locus 24 burned soil above the floors Loci 10 Chamber 2 and Locus 23 Chamber 3 floor.
Further Triple Colonnade collapse and vault collapse.
Closing elevation: 891.684 m in Chamber 2 (6.70 m in depth) and 891.834 m in Chamber 3 (6.55 m in depth).
Phase XII: Robbing and abandonment continue.
Phase XI: Further collapse post-CE 5th c. Possibly the result of the earthquake of CE 512.

The Munsell color of this deposit is a Reddish Yellow soil 5YR 6/6. This is a homogeneous destruction deposit, probably caused by earthquake with many architectural fragments as inclusions. Most of the inclusions are ashlars and architectural fragments mixed with coarse earth-sand, all of which are unevenly and randomly collapsed. This is a destruction level. The justification for assignment of field phase number is based on the fact that this deposit rests directly up against the walls of Chambers 2 and 3 and over the burning and debris associated above the floor mortar impressions, and with the exception of Locus 20, is later than any of the architectural features of Room 3 Chambers 2 and 3.
Dimensions: 13.43 m north south-by-4.10 m east west.
None in Chamber 3, Locus 1 in Chamber 2.
Phase XIII: Major collapses continue into the Islamic period.
